# Distributed Tracing Standards - OpenTelemetry 2025

Implement comprehensive distributed tracing using OpenTelemetry for end-to-end visibility across all services.

**Justification:** Distributed tracing reveals bottlenecks, dependencies, and failure points across complex microservice architectures.

## 🎯 Single Responsibility
This rule is ONLY responsible for trace collection and propagation. Not logging (see structured-logging) or metrics (see metrics-collection).

## 📋 Implementation Checklist

### Initial Setup
```markdown
- [ ] Install OpenTelemetry SDK and instrumentation
- [ ] Configure trace exporters (Jaeger/Zipkin/AWS X-Ray)
- [ ] Set up automatic instrumentation
- [ ] Implement manual instrumentation for business logic
- [ ] Configure sampling strategy
- [ ] Set up trace visualization (Jaeger UI/AWS X-Ray)
- [ ] Implement context propagation
- [ ] Configure trace retention policies
```

